  			<div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12"><h2>The long and short.</h2>
  			<p><i>"Welcome! <br><br>Thank you for your curiosity. I am glad that you have taken the time to visit my site, and to find out more about who I am, and what makes me…well, me. After 30 (alright alright, it’s more like 31) years on this earth, I believe I have garnered what can be considered some valuable life experience. And low and behold, I’m ready to share it! But what exactly makes my life experience shareable? Well, it’s your time to find out.</i></p>

			<p><i>Throughout your journey on this site, I hope that I can at least engage your curiosity further, past my credentials and <a class="links" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/shelbystanley" target="_blank">curriculum vitae</a>, drudging on through the trials and tribulations of my personal life (did I mention that I recently made a human?), and landing comfortably, I hope, at the connect with me page – because I’m always happy to be on the receiving end of a good conversation, or two.</i></p>
			
			<p><i>And maybe, just maybe, our paths may cross again, in the real world, and who knows what kind of trouble we can get into. Collaboration is a beautiful thing. Let’s try it sometime. 

			<br><br>Yours Truly,

			<br><br>Shelby Stanley</i>
			</p></div>
