		<section>
				<h2 id="Section3">Personal Life</h2>
				<img src="IMG/Shelby_Matthew_Engagement.jpg" alt="Shelby and Matthew's Engagement Shoot"width="250px" height="350px" class="img" class="col-lg-3 col-md-3 col-sm-3">
				<p class="col-lg-9 col-md-9 col-sm-9">It all began 30+ years ago…when Shelby came screaming into this world, one eye shut. Ask her mom about the story, she’d be thrilled to tell you. Born to immigrant parents, Shelby was raised on spicy food and soca music. She was never shy, pursuing her love of writing and polishing her stage presence at a very young age. She met her husband in grade school – yes, you read that right. They were in the same class in Grade 5. Shelby had a natural sense of humour at this time, coupled with a friendly attitude and acute athleticism (the latter not sticking around past middle-school). Serendipitously, despite moving away shortly thereafter, her partner re-emerged in her life 10 years later, and they’ve been together ever since.<br> <br> You’ll likely find Shelby talking to strangers – she loves to meet new people and find common ground! What’s next on her bucket list? Likely planning new and exciting adventures with her partner and daughter in tow, whether it be travelling the world, dining at unique and delectable restaurants, lounging at the beach in the summertime or hosting the odd party or two. She has two Shar Peis so you’ll always find a lint roller in her car. That, among other things of grave importance such as some form of scented air freshener because let’s face it, smell is the most intoxicating of senses.</p>

